        "In Aalen’s additive model, the primary objects of interest are _cumulative regression coefficients_: time-indexed functions that accumulate the effect of a covariate on the hazard as time progresses. Empirically, these functions are only identified at a discrete set of time points and are typically visualised as step functions that jump at event times.\n",
